Market Data

Overview

The Market Data module is responsible for collecting, normalizing, and distributing real-time and historical market information used throughout the AI Treasury Agent.

It provides pricing, liquidity, volatility, macroeconomic indicators, and on-chain metrics that enable the Portfolio Manager and Risk Engine to make informed treasury decisions.

The module acts as a trusted data layer and does not perform portfolio analysis or transaction execution.

Objectives

The Market Data module aims to:

Retrieve real-time token prices
Monitor liquidity across markets
Measure market volatility
Track macroeconomic indicators
Collect on-chain metrics
Normalize data from multiple providers
Deliver reliable market signals to downstream modules
Data Sources

