Data Refresh Strategy

Suggested update frequencies:

Data Type	Refresh Interval
Token Prices	Every 30–60 seconds
Wallet Valuations	Every 1 minute
Liquidity Metrics	Every 5 minutes
Gas Prices	Every 30 seconds
On-Chain Activity	Every 5 minutes
Macroeconomic Indicators	Daily
Reliability

To improve resilience, the module should:

Use multiple data providers
Cache recent responses
Retry failed requests
Detect stale data
Validate price anomalies
Log provider outages
Fall back to secondary sources when needed
Example Workflow
Fetch market prices from multiple providers.
Validate and normalize incoming data.
Retrieve liquidity and volatility metrics.
Collect on-chain indicators.
Generate market signals.
Publish normalized data to the Portfolio Manager and Risk Engine.
Security Considerations

The Market Data module should:

Never trust a single data provider
Validate abnormal price changes
Detect stale or missing data
Log all external API failures
Rate-limit provider requests
Monitor API availability
